						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Kharapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayagaṇḍagōpāla. Undated.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 4 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land in Tiruppāṟkaḍal, as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi>, along with the income from all levies to the deity Tirukkarapuram-uḍaiya nāyaṉār at Tiruppā ṟkaḍal, by <hi rend="bold">Vijayagaṇḍagōpāla</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Madhurāntaka-Pottappichchōḻa.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
